<Project Sdk="Microsoft.NET.Sdk">

  <!-- 069: the optional, packable effective-evidence *projection* — the evidence.json document leaf. A single
       pure, total `EvidenceJson.ofReport : EvidenceDocument -> string` (plus a `schemaVersion` constant) renders
       the already-folded effective-evidence world (declared + effective `EvidenceState` per node, the dependency
       edges, the freshness cause, and any named graph failure) into the deterministic, versioned `evidence.json`
       document text — the Governance-owned sibling of route.json / audit.json / verify.json /
       cache-eligibility.json.

       Where cache-eligibility.json is the per-change cache-reuse view, this evidence.json is the per-change
       EFFECTIVE-EVIDENCE view: for each node it carries BOTH the declared and the effective `EvidenceState`
       (taint surfaces as the visible delta, never a silent overwrite), the per-node freshness object naming
       *why* a node is stale/unresolved (or an honest `unknown`), and — when the graph is malformed — the named
       `GraphError` INSTEAD of a partial/guessed per-node map.

       PURE and TOTAL: no I/O, no git, no clock, never throws; byte-identical for identical input. It re-derives,
       re-classifies, re-runs, and re-orders NOTHING beyond the fixed field sequence and the documented stable
       sort of each collection. Every closed-DU token match is EXHAUSTIVE with NO wildcard, so a future
       EvidenceState / GraphError / freshness-cause case is a compile error here, never a silently mis-tokened
       field.

       It is a LEAF (research D7): it references ONLY FS.GG.Governance.Kernel (`EvidenceState`,
       `GraphError<'id>`) plus the freshness-cause vocabulary cores FS.GG.Governance.FreshnessResolution
       (`MissingFact`, `missingFactToken`) and FS.GG.Governance.EvidenceReuse (`RecomputeCause`); `InputCategory`
       / `categoryToken` arrive transitively (FreshnessKey). It takes NO command/host/Cli reference, so it cannot
       introduce a cycle (the CacheEligibilityJson -> CacheEligibility precedent). It adds NO new third-party
       PackageReference — serialization is the net10.0 shared-framework `System.Text.Json` (`Utf8JsonWriter`).
       Compile order is EvidenceJson.fsi -> EvidenceJson.fs: the curated public surface, then the pure
       projection. The whole surface is a pure total function — no MVU ceremony (Principle IV). -->
  <PropertyGroup>
    <RootNamespace>FS.GG.Governance.EvidenceJson</RootNamespace>
    <Version>0.1.0</Version>
    <IsPackable>true</IsPackable>
    <PackageId>FS.GG.Governance.EvidenceJson</PackageId>
  </PropertyGroup>

  <ItemGroup>
    <Compile Include="EvidenceJson.fsi" />
    <Compile Include="EvidenceJson.fs" />
  </ItemGroup>

  <ItemGroup>
    <ProjectReference Include="../FS.GG.Governance.Kernel/FS.GG.Governance.Kernel.fsproj" />
    <ProjectReference Include="../FS.GG.Governance.FreshnessResolution/FS.GG.Governance.FreshnessResolution.fsproj" />
    <ProjectReference Include="../FS.GG.Governance.EvidenceReuse/FS.GG.Governance.EvidenceReuse.fsproj" />
  </ItemGroup>


  <ItemGroup>
    <!-- 073: the shared deterministic-emit helper JsonText.writeToString (pure System.Text.Json leaf). -->
    <ProjectReference Include="../FS.GG.Governance.JsonText/FS.GG.Governance.JsonText.fsproj" />
  </ItemGroup>


  <ItemGroup>
    <!-- 073: the shared sub-object/map writers (pure JsonWriters leaf; module-qualified calls). -->
    <ProjectReference Include="../FS.GG.Governance.JsonWriters/FS.GG.Governance.JsonWriters.fsproj" />
  </ItemGroup>

</Project>
